                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="senses_multiple" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="oakley_sng_1" sensenum="1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1860-1926) a famous US <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/sharpshooter#sharpshooter_topg_1" title="sharpshooter definition"><span class="ndv">sharpshooter</span></a> <span class="gloss" htag="span" hclass="gloss">(= expert at shooting accurately)</span>. Her popular name was ‘Little Sure Shot’, because she was less than 5 feet/1.53 metres tall. She and her husband Frank Butler, also a sharpshooter, performed in <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/buffalo-bill#buffalo_bill_topg_1" title="Buffalo Bill's definition"><span class="ndv">Buffalo Bill's</span></a> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/wild-west-show#wild_west_show_topg_1" title="Wild West Show definition"><span class="ndv">Wild West Show</span></a>. The musical play and film <span class="ebi"><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/annie-get-your-gun" title="Annie Get Your Gun definition"><span class="ndv">Annie Get Your Gun</span></a></span> was based on her life.</span></span>          <div id="ring-links-box">
